{meta: title The Trail Of The Lonesome Pine}
{meta: artist Rex Allen}
{meta: composer Harry Carroll and Ballard Macdonald}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[F]In the Blue Ridge [D7]Mountains of [G7]Virginia
On the [C7]trail of the lonesome [F]pine
In the pale [D7]moon shine our [G7]hearts entwine
Where she carved her name and [C7]I carved mine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Oh [F]June like the mountains I'm blue
Like the [A]pine I am lonesome for [A7]you
In the [F]Blue Ridge [D7]Mountains of [G7]Virginia
On the [C7]trail of the lonesome [F]pine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
(We found [A7]love in the [D7]moonlight 
On the [G7]trail [C7]of the lonesome [F]pine)
{end_of_verse}

